    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect UCI indication copying in PUCCH/PUSCH handlers\n\n### Summary\nThe UCI indication copy functions in the NR FAPI interface were checking the destination PDU's bitmap instead of the source PDU's bitmap when deciding which optional fields to copy. This caused incorrect copying behavior when the destination structure contained uninitialized or stale bitmap values.\n\nSpecifically affected functions:\n- copy_uci_indication_PUCCH_0_1\n- copy_uci_indication_PUCCH_2_3_4  \n- copy_uci_indication_PUSCH\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain conditions where the destination UCI indication structure contained non-zero bitmap values before copying, the functions would attempt to copy SR/HARQ/CSI fields that were not present in the source, leading to:\n- Copying of garbage/uninitialized data\n- Potential segfaults when accessing invalid memory\n- Incorrect UCI reporting to higher layers\n\nThis issue was particularly evident during handover scenarios where UCI indication structures were reused between different UE contexts.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7_utils.c`: Updated all bitmap checks in UCI copy functions to reference `src->pduBitmap` instead of `dst->pduBitmap`\n"
}